The paper deals with the fundamental problem of approximating the diameter of directed or undirected graphs, which is a central topic in graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves computational geometry, as it deals with the geometric properties of graphs, so cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is another likely category. The paper also involves discrete mathematics (cs.DM) as it deals with combinatorial problems related to graphs. The paper also involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) as it deals with approximating the diameter of graphs. Finally, the paper involves complexity theory (cs.CC) as it provides evidence that a better approximation may be hard to obtain if we insist on an O(m^2) running time.
